comments: Eason (HOU) is moving alongside Bogdanovic's (DET) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.
Eason (HOU) establishes himself in Burks' (DET) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Martin Jr. (HOU) can't gain control of the loose ball and fumbles it out of bounds without being contacted by an opponent. Possession is correctly awarded to the Pistons.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Martin Jr.'s (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Smith Jr. (HOU) initiates contact with Burks' (DET) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
After the made free throw, Duren (DET) and Tate (HOU) engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Gordon (HOU) establishes himself in Ivey's (DET) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Burks (DET) moves alongside Tate's (HOU) path and collapses his arm in to absorb the marginal contact during the driving shot attempt.
Duren (DET) and Eason (HOU) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Tate (HOU) legally contests Ivey's (DET) jump shot attempt. Ivey's reaction is not commensurate with the level of contact.
Burks (DET) grabs and holds Tate (HOU), which affects his FOM off-ball.
Duren (DET) initiates contact with Martin Jr.'s (HOU) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Duren (DET) is retreating his arm into a vertical position and absorbs the marginal contact that occurs with Tate (HOU) during is putback shot attempt at the basket.
Duren (DET) establishes himself in Eason's (HOU) path and his legs remain within the frame of his body as contact occurs, which he does not deliver.
Smith Jr. (HOU) retreats along Burks' (DET) path and absorbs the contact as he makes clean contact with the ball to tie it up. A jump ball is correctly called.
Bogdanovic (DET) commits a take foul on Gordon (HOU).
Tate (HOU) moves alongside Ivey's (DET) path and removes his resting arm from Ivey's side as marginal contact occurs when Ivey gathers the ball during his driving shot attempt.
Stewart (DET) commits a take foul on Gordon (HOU).
Stewart (DET) establishes himself in Tate's (HOU) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Smith Jr. (HOU) legally contests Ivey's (DET) jump shot attempt.
